title: Mozzarella Cheese recipe in Tamil | How to make Mozzarella at home using Vinegar (without Rennet)
tags: mozzarella cheese recipe in tamil|mozzarella recipe in tamil|mozzarella without rennet|mozzarella with vinegar|cheese recipe in tamil|mozzarella cheese recipe|how to make mozzarella cheese|how to make mozzarella at home|mozzarella cheese in tamil|How to make Mozzarella at home using Vinegar|mozzarella without rennet in tamil|madras samayal|how to make cheese in tamil
description: In this video we will see how to make mozzarella cheese recipe in tamil. Mozzarella is traditionally made using rennet. However in this video we are going to see making mozzarella using rennet as well as making mozzarella using vinegar. The most important thing in making mozzarella is the selection of milk. The best milk is the milk fresh from farmers which has not been pasteurized or homogenized. The next best choice is using non-homogenized but pasteurized milk. The worst case is using homogenized and ultra-pasteurized milk (which makes very hard curds leading to paneer).The difference is also evident when melting these cheeses, the rennet made cheese melts at low temperatures and is very stretchy, the vinegar made cheese (+non-homogenized milk) does melt but takes a little longer and at a higher temperature however when homogenized milk is used in combination with vinegar it makes paneer. Friends, hope you found this recipe useful. All the best for making mozzarella at home. Also please do share your feedback about the recipe in the comments below. Happy cooking!

description: Subscribe to Sony Pal: http://www.youtube.com/sonypalindiaEpisode 540: The Values Of Life And Friendship-----------------------------------------The party gets canceled as Champaklal suddenly returns from his pilgrimage which makes the men sad. However, the men of Gokuldham society realize how much they value each other as friends. On the other hand, Champaklal is proud of Tapus decision to go bald and gives the family another valuable life lesson.About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:-------------------------------------------The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble for all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalaal.

description: Subscribe to Sony Pal: http://www.youtube.com/sonypalindiaEpisode 538: A Bold Step Of Getting Bald-----------------------------------------Tapu gets Bald despite everyone in the society requesting him to keep his beautiful hair. He proudly flaunts his bald head and refuses to give any reason for taking the step. As per Anjalis plan, Anjali, Tarak, Jethalal and Daya follow Tapu the next day to school to find out why he took such a drastic step.About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:-------------------------------------------The show is inspired by the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues that are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble for all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalaal.
